<subSubSection id="A7CC2DBDFFCFFFE4FF8DFE3BFC36FCE4" pageId="21" pageNumber="296" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFCFFFE4FF8DFE3BFBA1FD24" blockId="21.[113,1089,477,948]" pageId="21" pageNumber="296">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCFFFE4FF8DFE3BFF5EFE44" bold="true" box="[113,224,477,500]" pageId="21" pageNumber="296">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFCFFFE4FF1AFE3BFE26FE44" author="BOHEMAN" box="[230,408,477,500]" firstAuthor="BOHEMAN" pageId="21" pageNumber="296" refId="ref48022" refString="BOHEMAN C. H. 1862: Monographia Cassididarum. Tomus Quartus. (Supplementum). Officina Norstedtiana, Holmiae, vi + 504 pp." type="book" year="1862">BOHEMAN (1862)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFCFFFE4FDF7FE3BFD67FE44" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1862" box="[523,729,477,500]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="296" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="napaea">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCFFFE4FDF7FE3BFD67FE44" box="[523,729,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="296">Coptocycla napaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and compared it with 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFCFFFE4FC3BFE3BFF06FDA4" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="296" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sellata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCFFFE4FC3BFE3BFF06FDA4" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="296">Coptocycla sellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFCFFFE4FF3AFE1BFEE0FDA4" author="SPAETH" box="[198,350,509,532]" firstAuthor="SPAETH" pageId="21" pageNumber="296" pagination="1 - 108" refId="ref51203" refString="SPAETH F. 1926: Monographie der zu Gruppe der Coptocyclitae gehorigen amerikanischen Cassidinen (Col.): I. Die Gattungen mit gekammten Klauen. Supplementa Entomologica 13: 1 - 108." type="journal article" year="1926">SPAETH (1926)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized the latter with 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFCFFFE4FD6BFE1BFC19FDA4" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[663,935,509,532]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Microctenochira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="296" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCFFFE4FD6BFE1BFC19FDA4" box="[663,935,509,532]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="296">Microctenochira similata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and separated 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFCFFFE4FF8DFDFBFF5DFD84" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1862" box="[113,227,541,564]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="296" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="napaea">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCFFFE4FF8DFDFBFF5DFD84" box="[113,227,541,564]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="296">M. napaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the basal spot on pronotum with red (uniformly black in 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFCFFFE4FCA0FDFBFC6BFD84" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[860,981,541,564]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Microctenochira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="296" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCFFFE4FCA0FDFBFC6BFD84" box="[860,981,541,564]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="296">M. similata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and finer punctation of the central yellow spot on elytra. I have studied 
<typeStatus id="306DC094FFCFFFE4FD09FDDBFC93FDE4" box="[757,813,573,596]" pageId="21" pageNumber="296">types</typeStatus>
of all three taxa and in my opinion all belong to a single species and represent only colour forms. Moreover, 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFCFFFE4FC33FDBBFBFFFDC4" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1862" box="[975,1089,605,628]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="296" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="napaea">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCFFFE4FC33FDBBFBFFFDC4" box="[975,1089,605,628]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="296">M. napaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was based on a teneral specimen and as a result the punctation of its elytra appears finer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFCFFFE4FF6CFD7BFC36FCE4" blockId="21.[113,1089,477,948]" pageId="21" pageNumber="296">
I was able to locate 
<specimenCount id="F9D0B5BFFFCFFFE4FEA0FD7BFE46FD04" box="[348,504,669,692]" pageId="21" pageNumber="296" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFCFFFE4FDE4FD7BFD37FD04" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1862" box="[536,649,669,692]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="296" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="napaea">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFCFFFE4FDE4FD7BFD37FD04" box="[536,649,669,692]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="296">M. napaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that belong to the 
<typeStatus id="306DC094FFCFFFE4FCBBFD7BFCCBFD04" box="[839,885,669,692]" pageId="21" pageNumber="296">type</typeStatus>
series. The BMNH specimen, however, does not have a locality label, but is glued and pinned in the same way, on a similar label as other material collected by Clark during his travels in 
<collectingCountry id="97C13EA6FFCFFFE4FC5BFD3BFC52FD44" box="[935,1004,733,756]" name="Brazil" pageId="21" pageNumber="296">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. Only a small portion of the Cassidinae he collected is provided with original locality labels and if so, frequently only the first specimen in the original series had the label. Therefore I assume the specimen was collected in Petropolis as indicated by 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFCFFFE4FD2CFCDBFC3AFCE4" author="BOHEMAN" box="[720,900,829,852]" firstAuthor="BOHEMAN" pageId="21" pageNumber="296" refId="ref48022" refString="BOHEMAN C. H. 1862: Monographia Cassididarum. Tomus Quartus. (Supplementum). Officina Norstedtiana, Holmiae, vi + 504 pp." type="book" year="1862">BOHEMAN (1862)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
